gomodel:SYNGO_5519  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099699 replaced by GO:0097060" , "Rationale: Figure 3: ATG9A localizes to the membrane of small vesicles in COS7 cells co-expressing ATG9A-EGFP and mCherry-synapsin.\n\nFigure 4: Synaptophysin and ATG9A segregate in distinct vesicle clusters within the synapsin phase.\n\nFigure 8: \"When ATG9A-EGFP was co-expressed with synaptophysin-HA in cultured hippocampal neurons, the two proteins accumulated at distinct, although juxtaposed, spots at presynaptic sites (Fig. 8a, b), On the contrary, mCherry-SCAMP5 precisely colocalized with synaptophysin-HA at these sites (Fig. 8a, b). When ATG9A-EGFP, mCherry-synapsin and synaptophysin-HA were co-expressed together, the juxtaposed spots of ATG9A-EGFP and of synaptophysin-HA were both positive for synapsin as we had observed in fibroblasts (Fig. 4a), although, again as in fibroblasts, synapsin was more concentrated in the synaptophysin-region (Fig. 8c).\". Experimental description: Figure 8: \"Mouse hippocampal neuronal cultures were transfected as indicated and imaged at DIV14-17\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_5519" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

